{"word":"κατεῖδον","slug":"κατεῖδον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κατεῖδον</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <el>κατ-ῐδεῖν</el>) (<a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <el>κατιδών</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>aor2 with no <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> in use, <a href='S:καθοράω'><el>καθοράω</el></a> being used instead\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to look down</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to look down upon</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>: simply <i>to behold, regard, perceive</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>κατιδεῖν βίον</el> to live, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>—Also in aor2 <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a> <el>κατειδόμην</el>, <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <el>κατιδέσθαι</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}